{
  "stem": "11272.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when I went to the US Museum, Holocaust Museum in Washington, my daughter finally pulled me away after half an hour-- I kept on looking and looking and looking to that cattle car that they brought in as a sample, because I couldn't figure out how in the world they managed to cram so many of us in there.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's true we couldn't move.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We couldn't turn.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you could only stand up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And hell broke loose after half an hour, because there were people who-- there were teeny little babies.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They might have been a week, two week, three weeks old.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Those babies were crying.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They wanted to be fed, and in those days there were no bottles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So obviously these women were very religious, and they didn't want to be exposing themselves to people around them until there was no choice.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we tried very desperately to turn around, not to embarrass these women, but we couldn't.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was no room.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And if that wasn't bad enough, the little boys, after two, three hours, had to make wee-wee, and they started crying.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the little girls, the same thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So they started wee-weeing on the next person or in their pants.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then the next thing, the elderly couldn't stand on their feet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They started collapsing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So there was shoving and screaming and crying to try to protect that nobody should step on their heads.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And this went on and on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the thing that sticks most in my mind about that ride, suddenly my father-- may he rest in peace-- was a very, very strict man-- he never, never asked me anything twice-- suddenly started pleading with me in Yiddish, Yankele, [SPEAKING YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I looked at him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I was no different.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
